ampaign faculty from the gspm senior political consultants with experience on presidential campaigns and political scientists analyze the strategy and tactics of the candidates in the primaries and general election the surge in youth voting new communication tools and the extraordinary amount of money raised a second volume in the series is campaigning in the twentyfirst century a whole new ballgame routledge december  authored by dennis johnson this work will explore the various ways that professional campaigns from the presidency down to local contests have changed during the past decade dr johnson has been at the forefront of scholars examining the role of professional consultants and political management he was editor of a major reference book the routledge handbook on political management routledge  which brought together fortynine scholars and practitioners from throughout the world to focus on applied politics elections and issue management a second edition of his no place for amateurs how political consultants are reshaping american democracy routledge appeared in  he has also contributed chapters to books and peerreviewed journals on political consulting “campaigning in the twentyfirst century change and continuity in american political marketing” in jennifer leesmarshment ed routledge handbook on political marketing routledge  forthcoming “campaigning on the internet” a chapter in stephen c craig ed the electoral challenge theory meets practice cq press  “first hurdles the evolution of the preprimary and primary stages of american presidential elections” a chapter in bruce i newman and philip davies eds winning elections with political marketing haworth  “ elections perspectives on the closest presidential election in us history” a chapter in bruce i newman and dejan vercic eds communication of politics haworth  “perspectives on political consulting” journal of political marketing  october  and “the business of political consulting” a chapter in james a thurber ed campaign warriors brookings  dr johnson also serves as senior editor of the journal of political marketing routledge and on the editorial board of the journal of public affairs wiley dr johnson also has written about the impact of online technology on politics and political institutions from  he was principal investigator of a major study of congress and online communication funded by the pew charitable trusts he wrote congress online bridging the gap between citizens and their representatives routledge  other writings include “grassroots astroturf and internet lobbying” in burdett loomis ed lobbying in the united states cq press  forthcoming “communicating with congress” a chapter in james a thurber and colton campbell eds congress and the internet cq books  “us congress responds to online communications needs” in journal of political marketing  october  “elections and public polling will the media get online polling right” journal of psychology and marketing  november  and “the cyberspace election in your future” a chapter in bruce i newman ed political marketing handbook sage  dr johnson serves on the editorial board of the journal of information technology and politics he is author of the laws that shaped america fifteen acts of congress and their lasting impact routledge  a major work on the history of american domestic public policy johnson has presented papers or delivered speeches at the sixtieth annual british political studies conference edinburgh  the fiftyfourth annual british american studies conference university of leicester  the sixth annual political marketing conference middlesex university london  gspmsponsored conferences on elections in madrid  the eighth international public relations symposium lake bled slovenia  the midwest association of public opinion research chicago  the world congress of international association of political consultants vienna  and milan  and the european association of political consultants palermo  dr johnson has guest lectured and participated in seminars at the judge institute of management studies cambridge university england  and the university of innsbruck austria  he has been interviewed by a wide variety of television and newspaper sources including the new york times the washington post nbc evening news british broadcasting corporation canadian broadcasting corporation cspan public broadcasting system msnbc us information agency voice of america middle east television japan broadcasting corporation and ap television as fulbright distinguished lecturer he is currently lecturing and speaking widely to a variety of academic professional and business audiences throughout china college of professional studies  st street nw suite  washington dc  phone   fax  cpsgwuedu home  contact us  maps  directions  directory  site map campus advisories nondiscrimination policy privacy policy terms of use copyright contact gw az index